text: The whole plot to make this a sad movie is that she was in a car crash with her whole family and if she comes out of the coma she's in she won't have any family left. And in the meantime she's in a made up place called purgatory which means she's wondering the earth as a type of ghost. Yet what i hate about this film is that the girl has gone out with a typical movie boyfriend. They have no reason to be together. The only thing they're together for is the fact that she's a wicked hot teenage girl and the teenage boy is in a band and plays the guitar. There relationship is just so bloody fake, even though we know it's just a movie anyway, but that just wouldn't happen in real life. Unless the girl was a bloody whore. And the girls boyfriend goes to the hospital and says, "I'm still here, and I'm crazy in-love with you. Please stay.". OK, that just has to make you think, because most guys really just want a girlfriend for sex, and look how sexy she is. No bloody wonder he wants her to stay. Not that, that's how i see girls, but that's how i see most guys. And this guy seems to be able to get any girl he wants, so the reality is, he could just get another girlfriend. But of course not, this is a movie don't be so ridiculous mate....
